prompts.text:
Add a new Oracle SQLcl connection with these details:
- Connection name: ${arguments.name}
- Host: ${arguments.host}
- Port: ${arguments.port}
- Service name: ${arguments.service}
- Username: ${arguments.username}
- Password: ${arguments.password}

Use the run-sqlcl tool and execute: connect -savepwd -save ${arguments.name} ${arguments.username}/${arguments.password}@${arguments.host}:${arguments.port}/${arguments.service}

After executing, verify the connection was added by listing all connections.

Rename the Oracle SQLcl connection '${arguments.old_name}' to '${arguments.new_name}'.

Use the run-sqlcl tool and execute: connmgr rename -conn ${arguments.old_name} ${arguments.new_name}

After executing, verify by listing all connections.
